Oh no! Burnt New York Style Cheesecake! This is the first bake. I wrote the recipe yesterday. I was so sure it would work! But oh well, time to make some adjustments. I baked this at on 140C for 75 minutes and it looked golden when it was done, jiggly in the centre but I think the oven was too hot as it was cooling with the door slightly open which is one way you can stop cracking. I also want a taller cheesecake. So I’m going to make more filling, bake on a lower temperature for 90 minutes and see how we go! Hoping to have this one up on the blog next week for you guys to try!

There are a couple simple things you can do to get perfect patisserie style eclairs at home!

1. Use bread flour – you can use all-purpose but I feel like bread flour gives you a stronger, crisper éclair.

2. Use a French star tip to pipe your eclairs. It helps the eclairs rise and bake in a nice even shape with no cracks. I used a 1.2cm / 1/2-inch French star tip. Pipe them 10cm in length, pipe the ends slightly wider than the middle.

3. Dust with powdered sugar – to get a nice crisp and slightly sweetened golden-brown éclair.

Recipe linked in my bio!

That’s it! No more cup measurements!!! I’ve had too many people telling me my recipes don’t work. I know they work because I test them! Here’s three big reasons why I’m not going to have cup measurements on my website anymore:

1. Cup sizes differ in Australia compared to America. American cups are slightly smaller which makes a huge difference in baking!

2. The way you pack your cup with ingredients matters. For example you shouldn’t just scoop flour into a cup. You’re supposed to scoop into the cup using a spoon and then level off. I can’t rely on everyone to know the correct way to measure using cups. Why would you do that when measuring using kitchen scales is so much easier, quicker and more precise?

3. You get the exact same results every single time when you measure by weight. Cups can often do give you different results each tine.

NO MORE CUPS! Even liquids will be in weight measurements. No more effing cups!!! Get yourself kitchen scales. 😂

Let’s say I shared my second batch in cup measurements. I would have to rely on everyone knowing hope to measure ingredients properly using the scoop and level method. Even then, everyone will get different amounts of flour in their cookie dough. This is the difference between 25g flour of flour in a cookie recipe. Following Erin from @cloudykitchen ‘s lead in showing why measuring by weight is so much better!

Here's my Top 3 tips for make a FOOL PROOF Pavlova!

1. let it cool in the oven COMPLETELY! And don't open the oven door at all!
2. make sure your bowl and beaters are super clean, I clean mine with white vinegar. And don't get egg yolk in the meringue!
3. Use a non-alcahol based vanilla extract. I've found alcahol based extracts can mess with a meringues stability.
